Interested in becoming an Associate at Pegasus Capital Advisors? Learn more about our Associate program. 


Learn More










Pegasus' Associate program offers highly qualified candidates the chance to engage with middle market companies across a range of industries on a global basis. Associates should have at least two years of prior investment banking, consulting or private equity work experience. Our approach is unique among peer private equity firms, enabling an entrepreneurial, well-rounded experience with significant responsibility and direct reporting.
Associates are integral to our deal teams and often work directly with the senior leadership of Pegasus on all aspects of new investments and portfolio management including but not limited to financial analysis and modeling, deal structuring, transaction due diligence, industry research, competitive analysis, drafting of formal investment committee presentations and portfolio monitoring. Associates will work on a wide range of transactions including acquisitions, divestitures, restructurings, recapitalizations, joint ventures and management buyouts.















