Example Projects
Since 2000, Pegasus Capital has worked with a diverse  group of clients in a variety of fields.  Below is a sampling of these assignments. Contract bookkeeping & CFO ServicesSeveral start-ups and small businesses have used Pegasus on both a temporary and permanent basis to handle  their accounting.An internet consulting firm hired Pegasus to organize and clean up their financial statements after they  received an IRS garnishment.An energy services company used Pegasus to process customer refunds to take advantage of Pegasus’s lower  transaction costs.Financial Analysis & Planning   A large utility hired Pegasus  to investigate the viability of the utility becoming an internet service provider.A regional venture capital fund engaged Pegasus to evaluate potential equity investment.Crisis & Turnaround ManagementThe Bankruptcy Court appointed Pegasus as a Chapter 11 Trustee to reorganizing a Kentucky farm supply company.Pegasus renegotiated equipment loans and leases for a regional trucking firm.        On behalf of creditors, Pegasus managed and ultimately liquidated over 40 rental properties owned by a failing real estate holding company. Business DevelopmentPegasus worked with a wood manufacturer to expand on a regional basis.Pegasus aided a telecommunications consulting firm in securing clients and investigating new markets.  Systems DevelopmentAn appliance repair service contracted with Pegasus to develop an accounting system to handle non-standard  transactions.Raising CapitalPegasus arranged debt financing for a recording studio.Pegasus has written numerous business plans and loan package used by clients to obtain financing.  Sample clients include an established hotel operator, a large boat manufacturer, a rural gas station, and a start-up environmentally friendly packaging company. Energy OptimizationFleet analysis for natural gas and propane vehicles.Implementation of the KY Energy Direct Pay program (see next webpage.)









